WorkItem.Description:
Typescript compiler chokes when returning an object literal if it starts on a new line.

Works fine if the object literal opening brace is on the same line as "return".

```
        // --- This works fine
        private Works(): { x: number; }
        {
            return {
                x: 3
            }
        }

        // --- This won't compile
        private DoesntWork(): { x: number; }
        {
            return
            {
                x: 3
            }
        }

```
Error message: "Function declared a non-void return type, but has no return expression"
